Filing Pleadings with Court Clerk

1. Prepare the Pleadings - Make sure all necessary documents are complete and accurate. - Review the local court rules for specific requirements. 2. Make Copies - Ensure you have enough copies for all parties involved. - Keep a copy for your records. 3. Visit the Court Clerk - Go to the courthouse during business hours. - Submit the pleadings to the court clerk for filing. - Pay any necessary filing fees. 4. Get Stamped Copies - Once filed, make sure to get stamped copies as proof of filing. - Keep these stamped copies in a safe place. 5. Serve the Other Parties - Serve the filed pleadings on all other parties involved in the case. - Follow the proper service methods required by law. 6. File Proof of Service - File proof of service with the court clerk once all parties have been served. - This ensures that the court has a record of proper service. 7. Follow Up - Check the case docket regularly for updates. - Follow up with the court clerk if there are any issues or delays.
